  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and organizations that work to combat money laundering:\n\n1. Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- An intergovernmental organization setting global standards\n- Develops recommendations to prevent money laundering\n- Monitors countries' compliance with anti-money laundering (AML) standards\n\n2. United Nations Conventions\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- UN Convention against Corruption\n- Provide frameworks for international cooperation in fighting money laundering\n\n3. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- Sets international banking regulations\n- Provides guidelines for preventing money laundering in financial institutions\n\n4. International Monetary Fund (IMF)\n- Helps countries develop AML/counter-terrorist financing frameworks\n- Provides technical assistance and training\n\n5. Individual Country Laws\n- Most countries have their own domestic anti-money laundering laws\n- Many follow FATF recommendations\n- Examples include:\n  - U.S. Bank Secrecy Act\n  - European Union's Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n\nThese international efforts aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds and moving money through the global financial system.",
